  "subject": "feat: iceberg maintenance cronworkflow and pipeline alerts",
  "body": "Plan 2 Task 5 (design D12 + D11 extension):\n\n- maintenance.py: weekly snapshot expiry for every table registered in the\n  alice namespace, via table.maintenance.expire_snapshots().older_than(...)\n  .commit() -- verified live against the pinned pyiceberg 0.11.1 (a\n  throwaway venv confirmed the exact API shape; table.manage_snapshots()\n  is a different, branch/tag operation, not used). The API exists on this\n  pin, so the brief's BLOCKED-alternative (detect-and-report, defer to\n  Trino OPTIMIZE) does not apply -- physical file GC still defers to Plan\n  3's Trino OPTIMIZE, since this pin's MaintenanceTable has no orphan-file\n  removal method.\n\n- ingest-maintenance CronWorkflow (weekly, Sunday 04:00), same\n  pipeline-runner/ttlStrategy pattern as ingest-nightly/ingest-sitesonar.\n\n- datalake-pipeline PrometheusRule group: WorkflowFailed, IcebergIngestStale,\n  RetentionUnverifiedRows. Metric names verified live against the real\n  argo-workflows-workflow-controller /metrics (port-forwarded, since the\n  controller image has no wget/curl) -- argo_workflows_total_count is the\n  only per-namespace/per-phase counter, argo_workflows_cronworkflows_triggered_total\n  the only metric with a per-CronWorkflow name label; no per-workflow\n  succeeded-timestamp metric exists on this controller version, and\n  kube-state-metrics exposes nothing for the Workflow/CronWorkflow CRDs\n  either (checked live, ruling out the brief's kube_job-style fallback\n  hypothesis). RetentionUnverifiedRows deliberately shares WorkflowFailed's\n  exact expr (no Pushgateway, no new component) -- documented explicitly in\n  its annotation rather than hidden.\n\n- sitesonar.py: file-level high-water-mark skip (scoped in from the P2T4\n  review) via dlt.current.resource_state(), closing the \"re-downloads the\n  full backlog every run\" gap. TDD: select_files_to_fetch (pure filter) +\n  _iter_rows's state wiring.\n\n- hack/kind-verify.sh: alert-rules probe now also asserts WorkflowFailed\n  loaded, proving the new PrometheusRule group hydrated alongside the\n  original datalake group.\n\ningest/tests: 89 passed (was 65; +12 maintenance, +12 sitesonar).\n"
}
